msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:131
#, no-wrap
msgid "In the \"Prerequisites and Assumptions\" section, we mentioned that we will be using the [Apache Sites Enabled](../web/apache-sites-enabled.md) procedure for our configuration. Click over to that procedure and set up the basics there, and then return to this document to continue.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:133
#, no-wrap
msgid "For Nextcloud, we will need to create the following configuration file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "vi /etc/httpd/sites-available/com.yourdomain.nextcloud\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "Your configuration file should look something like this:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:140
#, no-wrap
msgid "<VirtualHost *:80>\n"
"  DocumentRoot /var/www/sub-domains/com.yourdomain.nextcloud/html/\n"
"  ServerName  nextcloud.yourdomain.com\n"
"  <Directory /var/www/sub-domains/com.yourdomain.nextcloud/html/>\n"
"    Require all granted\n"
"    AllowOverride All\n"
"    Options FollowSymLinks MultiViews\n"
"    <IfModule mod_dav.c>\n"
"      Dav off\n"
"    </IfModule>\n"
"  </Directory>\n"
"</VirtualHost>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:156
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once done, save your changes (with `SHIFT:wq!` for _vi_).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:158
#, no-wrap
msgid "Next, create a link to this file in /etc/httpd/sites-enabled:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:159
#, no-wrap
msgid "ln -s /etc/httpd/sites-available/com.yourdomain.nextcloud /etc/httpd/sites-enabled/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:163
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating The Directory"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:166
#, no-wrap
msgid "As noted in the configuration above, the _DocumentRoot_ needs to be created. This can be done by:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:167
#, no-wrap
msgid "mkdir -p /var/www/sub-domains/com.yourdomain.com/html\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:172
#, no-wrap
msgid "This is where our Nextcloud instance will be installed.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:174
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring PHP"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:177
#, no-wrap
msgid "We need to set the time zone for PHP. To do this, open up php.ini with your text editor of choice:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:178
#, no-wrap
msgid "vi /etc/opt/remi/php80/php.ini\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:183
#, no-wrap
msgid "Then find the line:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:184
#, no-wrap
msgid ";date.timezone =\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:189
#, no-wrap
msgid "We need to remove the remark (;) and set our time zone. For our example time zone, we would put in either:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:190
#, no-wrap
msgid "date.timezone = \"America/Chicago\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:195
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:262
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:191
#: ../src/docs/guides/contribute/rockydocs_webdev_v2.md:125
#, no-wrap
msgid "OR\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:196
#, no-wrap
msgid "date.timezone = \"US/Central\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:201
#, no-wrap
msgid "Then save and exit the php.ini file.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:203
#, no-wrap
msgid "Note that for the sake of keeping things the same, your time zone in the _php.ini_ file should match up to your machine's time zone setting. You can find out what this is set to by doing the following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:204
#, no-wrap
msgid "ls -al /etc/localtime\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:209
#, no-wrap
msgid "Which should show you something like this, assuming you set your time zone when you installed Rocky Linux and are living in the Central time zone:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:210
#, no-wrap
msgid "/etc/localtime -> /usr/share/zoneinfo/America/Chicago\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:214
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring mariadb-server"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:217
#, no-wrap
msgid "Set _mariadb-server_ to start on boot:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:218
#, no-wrap
msgid "systemctl enable mariadb\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:223
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/dokuwiki_server.md:181
#, no-wrap
msgid "And then start it:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:224
#, no-wrap
msgid "systemctl restart mariadb\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:229
#, no-wrap
msgid "Again, as indicated earlier, we will be using the setup procedure for hardening _mariadb-server_ found [here](../database/database_mariadb-server.md) for the initial configuration.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:230
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing .zip"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:233
#, no-wrap
msgid "The next few steps assume that you are remotely connected to your Nextcloud server via _ssh_ with a remote console open:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:240
#, no-wrap
msgid "Navigate to the [Nextcloud web site](https://nextcloud.com/).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:240
#, no-wrap
msgid "Let your mouse hover over \"Get Nextcloud\" which will bring up a drop-down menu.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:240
#, no-wrap
msgid "Click on \"Server Packages\".\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:240
#, no-wrap
msgid "Right-click on \"Download Nextcloud\" and copy the link address (the exact syntax of this is different browser to browser).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:240
#, no-wrap
msgid "In your remote console on the Nextcloud server, type \"wget\" and then a space and paste in what you just copied. You should get something like the following: `wget https://download.nextcloud.com/server/releases/nextcloud-21.0.1.zip` (note that the version could be different).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:240
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once you hit enter, the download of the .zip file will start and will be completed fairly quickly.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:242
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once the download is complete, unzip the Nextcloud zip file by using the following:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:243
#, no-wrap
msgid "unzip nextcloud-21.0.1.zip\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:247
#, no-wrap
msgid "Copying Content And Changing Permissions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:250
#, no-wrap
msgid "After completing the unzip step, you should now have a new directory in /root called \"nextcloud.\" Change into this directory:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:251
#, no-wrap
msgid "cd nextcloud\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:256
#, no-wrap
msgid "And either copy or move the content to our _DocumentRoot_:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:257
#, no-wrap
msgid "cp -Rf * /var/www/sub-domains/com.yourdomain.nextcloud/html/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:263
#, no-wrap
msgid "mv * /var/www/sub-domains/com.yourdomain.nextcloud/html/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:268
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now that everything is where it should be, the next step is to make sure that apache owns the directory. To do this, run:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:269
#, no-wrap
msgid "chown -Rf apache.apache /var/www/sub-domains/com.yourdomain.nextcloud/html\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:274
#, no-wrap
msgid "For security reasons, we also want to move the \"data\" folder from inside to outside of the _DocumentRoot_. Do this with the following command:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:275
#, no-wrap
msgid "mv /var/www/sub-domains/com.yourdomain.nextcloud/html/data /var/www/sub-domains/com.yourdomain.nextcloud/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:280
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring Nextcloud"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:283
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now comes the fun! First, make sure that you have your services running. If you followed the above steps, they should already be running. We have had several steps between those initial service starts, so let's go ahead and restart them, just to be sure:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:284
#, no-wrap
msgid "systemctl restart httpd\n"
"systemctl restart mariadb\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:290
#, no-wrap
msgid "If everything restarts and there are no issues, then you are ready to move on.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:292
#, no-wrap
msgid "To do the initial configuration, we want to actually load the site in a web browser:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:293
#, no-wrap
msgid "http://nextcloud.yourdomain.com/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:298
#, no-wrap
msgid "Assuming that you've done everything correctly so far, you should be presented with a Nextcloud setup screen:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:300
#, no-wrap
msgid "![nextcloud login screen](../images/nextcloud_screen.jpg)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:302
#, no-wrap
msgid "There are a couple of things that we want to do differently than the defaults that show up:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "At the top of the web page, where it says \"Create an admin account\", set the user and password. For the sake of this document, we are entering \"admin\" and setting a strong password. Remember to save this somewhere safe (like a password manager) so that you don't lose it! Even though you have typed into this field, don't hit 'Enter' until we have done all of the setup fields!\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "Under the \"Storage & database\" section, change the \"Data folder\" location from the default document root, to where we moved the data folder earlier: `/var/www/sub-domains/com.yourdomain.nextcloud/data`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "Under the \"Configure the database\" section, change from \"SQLite\" to \"MySQL/MariaDB\" by clicking on that button.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "Type the MariaDB root user and password that you set earlier into the \"Database user\" and \"Database password\" fields.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "In the \"Database name\" field, type \"nextcloud\".\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:309
#, no-wrap
msgid "In the \"localhost\" field, type \"localhost:3306\" (3306 is the default _mariadb_ connect port).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:311
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once you have all this, click `Finish Setup` and you should be up and running.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:313
#, no-wrap
msgid "The browser window will refresh for a bit and then usually not reload the site. Enter your URL in the browser window again and you should be confronted with the default first pages.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:315
#, no-wrap
msgid "Your administrative user is already (or should be) logged in at this point, and there are several informational pages designed to get you up to speed. The \"Dashboard\" is what users will see when they first login. The administrative user can now create other users, install other applications and many other tasks.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:317
#, no-wrap
msgid "The \"Nextcloud Manual.pdf\" file is the user manual, so that users can get familiar with what is available. The administrative user should read through or at least scan the high points of the admin manual [On the Nextcloud web site](https://docs.nextcloud.com/server/21/admin_manual/)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:321
#, no-wrap
msgid "At this point, don't forget that this is a server that you will be storing company data on. It's important to get it locked down with a firewall, get the [backup set up](../backup/rsnapshot_backup.md), secure the site with an [SSL](../security/generating_ssl_keys_lets_encrypt.md), and any other duties that are required to keep your data safe.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/guides/cms/cloud_server_using_nextcloud.md:323
#, no-wrap
msgid "A decision to take the company cloud in house is one that needs to be evaluated carefully. For those that decide that keeping company data locally is preferable over an external cloud host, Nextcloud is a good alternative.\n"
msgstr ""

